---
import Layout from './layout.astro'
import { getAssetPrefix } from '../../../../utils/path.js'
---

<Layout
  title="Post - No Sidebar"
  description="A clean, responsive theme designed to help homeowners associations build a strong online presence."
>
  <!-- Post Content -->
  <section class="bg-body py-5">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
          <!-- Blog Heading, Category, and Date -->
          <div class="mb-4" data-aos="fade-down" data-aos-duration="800">
            <span class="badge text-body bg-primary-subtle fs-6 mb-2">Landscaping</span>
            <h1 class="mb-2">Spring Landscaping Tips for a Greener Neighborhood</h1>
            <p class="text-muted"><i class="ri-calendar-line me-1"></i>12 Jan 2025</p>
          </div>

          <!-- Cover Image -->
          <div class="mb-4" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100" data-aos-duration="800">
            <img
              src={getAssetPrefix('/assets/img/theme-images/img-3.jpg')}
              alt="Blog Cover"
              class="img-fluid rounded"
              style="max-height: 400px; object-fit: cover; width: 100%;"
            />
          </div>

          <!-- Blog Content -->
          <div class="mb-4" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200" data-aos-duration="800">
            <p>
              As the weather warms up and the days grow longer, spring is the perfect time to give
              your yard a little attention and help our neighborhood look its best. Whether you're a
              seasoned gardener or just starting out, a few simple changes can make a big difference
              in your curb appeal—and support our community's shared goals for a clean, welcoming
              environment.
            </p>
            <p>
              Start by clearing away any fallen leaves, twigs, and debris left over from the winter
              months. A clean lawn instantly looks more inviting and gives you a fresh canvas for
              planting. Consider refreshing your mulch—it not only makes flower beds look tidy but
              also helps retain soil moisture and control weeds as the temperatures rise.
            </p>
            <p>
              If you're adding new plants, choose native or drought-resistant options when possible.
              These plants require less water and care, making them a smart and eco-friendly choice.
              Flowers like black-eyed susans or coneflowers thrive in many climates and add vibrant
              color to your yard with minimal effort.
            </p>
            <p>
              Finally, take a moment to edge your lawn, trim any overgrown bushes, and inspect your
              irrigation system if you have one. Small maintenance tasks like these go a long way
              toward creating a neat, well-kept appearance that benefits the whole community.
            </p>
            <p>
              Let’s work together to make our neighborhood shine this spring—one yard at a time!
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Share Button -->
          <div class="mb-4" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="300" data-aos-duration="800">
            <button class="btn btn-lg btn-outline-primary rounded-pill px-3">
              <i class="ri-share-line me-1"></i>Share this post
            </button>
          </div>

          <!-- Author Section -->
          <div
            class="d-flex align-items-center border-top pt-4 mb-5"
            data-aos="fade-up"
            data-aos-delay="400"
            data-aos-duration="800"
          >
            <img
              src={getAssetPrefix('/assets/img/avatars/avatar11.jpg')}
              alt="Author Image"
              class="rounded-circle me-3"
              width="64"
              height="64"
            />
            <div>
              <h6 class="fs-5 mb-1">
                <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none text-body">James Mitchell</a>
              </h6>

              <p class="text-muted mb-0">President of Longhorn Heights HOA.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Similar Posts -->
          <div class="mb-4" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="500" data-aos-duration="800">
            <h4 class="mb-4">Similar Posts</h4>
            <div class="row g-4">
              <div class="col-md-6">
                <div
                  class="card border h-100 p-0"
                  data-aos="flip-up"
                  data-aos-delay="100"
                  data-aos-duration="800"
                >
                  <img
                    src={getAssetPrefix('/assets/img/theme-images/img-2.jpg')}
                    class="card-img-top"
                    style="max-height: 150px; object-fit: cover;"
                    alt="Similar Post 1"
                  />
                  <div class="card-body p-3">
                    <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none text-body"
                      ><h5 class="card-title">
                        Pool Reopening Schedule and New Rules for Summer
                      </h5></a
                    >
                    <p class="card-text text-muted mb-2">
                      Everything you need to know about the pool's reopening and updated guidelines.
                    </p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-link text-body p-0">Read more</a>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-6">
                <div
                  class="card border h-100 p-0"
                  data-aos="flip-up"
                  data-aos-delay="200"
                  data-aos-duration="800"
                >
                  <img
                    src={getAssetPrefix('/assets/img/theme-images/img-1.jpg')}
                    class="card-img-top"
                    style="max-height: 150px; object-fit: cover;"
                    alt="Similar Post 2"
                  />
                  <div class="card-body p-3">
                    <a href="#" class="text-decoration-none text-body"
                      ><h5 class="card-title">
                        How to Submit a Maintenance Request the Right Way
                      </h5></a
                    >
                    <p class="card-text text-muted mb-2">
                      A step-by-step guide to getting common area issues resolved quickly.
                    </p>
                    <a href="#" class="btn btn-link text-body p-0">Read more</a>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Newsletter Section -->
  <section class="text-bg-primary py-5">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <!-- Heading and Intro -->
      <h2 class="fs-1 mb-2" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-duration="800">Stay Connected</h2>
      <p class="mb-4" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100" data-aos-duration="800">
        Sign up for updates about community news, upcoming events, and important HOA announcements.
      </p>
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2">
          <!-- Form -->
          <form
            class="row g-4 justify-content-center"
            data-aos="fade-up"
            data-aos-delay="200"
            data-aos-duration="1000"
          >
            <!-- Name Field -->
            <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
              <input
                type="text"
                class="form-control form-control-lg"
                placeholder="Your Name"
                required
              />
            </div>
            <!-- Phone Field -->
            <div class="col-12 col-md-6">
              <input
                type="tel"
                class="form-control form-control-lg"
                placeholder="Phone Number"
                pattern="[0-9\-+()\s]{7,15}"
                required
              />
            </div>
            <!-- Email Field -->
            <div class="col-12">
              <input
                type="email"
                class="form-control form-control-lg"
                placeholder="Email Address"
                required
              />
            </div>
            <!-- Submit Button -->
            <div class="col-12 col-md-auto">
              <button type="submit" class="btn btn-lg btn-dark w-100">
                Subscribe<i class="ri-arrow-right-line ms-2"></i>
              </button>
            </div>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
